{\n  "title": "[PHASE 1] Load cleaned data from GCS into MySQL",\n  "body": "## Description\nAfter cleaning, load processed records from GCS into MySQL expenses table, with lookup/insert for categories and merchants.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] db_loader.py created with load_expenses_to_mysql(df)\n- [ ] Categories looked up or inserted by name, returning category_id\n- [ ] Merchants looked up or inserted by name, returning merchant_id\n- [ ] Rows inserted into expenses table\n- [ ] Deduplication logic in place (expense_date + amount + description)\n- [ ] time_dim populated for all dates in dataset\n- [ ] ingest.py updated to call db_loader after cleaning\n\n## Technical Notes\nUse SQLAlchemy + pymysql. Avoid duplicate inserts on re-upload.\n\n## Related Files / Components\n- ingestion/python_api/services/db_loader.py (new)\n- ingestion/python_api/routers/ingest.py (update)\n- database/schema/init.sql\n\n## Phase\n- [x] Phase 1 – Ingestion\n\n## Checklist\n- [ ] Code changes implemented\n- [ ] Tests written/updated\n- [ ] Documentation updated\n- [ ] PR linked to this issue\n}","message":"Create new issue: Load cleaned data from GCS into MySQL","owner":"thoness-nguyen","path":".github/issues/1.json","repo":"personal-finance-pipeline"}